node.text:
⁣
⁣
The big THIRTY TWO 👨🏽‍🦳 I hope you have the best day (that is inevitable because I’m cooking a breakfast and dinner for you) and that you enjoy this little compilation as much as I enjoyed putting it together! Thank you for being you, you’re the best and I can’t wait to make many more fun memories together until we are rocking in our rocking chairs 😝! I love you millionssssss ♥️🥰

node.title: Happy day of birth to this hunk of a husband 🧐😍

Take your training to the next level with our Extreme workouts, now available for the gym and home on the Strongandsxy fitness app!

No matter your level of fitness, we have a plan for you! Click the link in our bio to take advantage of our 50% OFF subscriptions SALE. 💥 

www.strongandsxy.com

#StrongandSxy 💪🏼💗
#StrongandSxyApp
#getfitwithStrongandSxy
#homeworkouts
#fitnessjourney

OUTFIT: @gymshark

⁣⁣
🔸 50% off ALL subscription prices for the @strongandsxy fitness app AND the home workout guides. Once you pay this discounted price for the Strong&Sxy fitness app, that’s what you’ll continue to pay so it’s a great time to get a subscription! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🔴 IMPORTANT:⁣⁣
YOU WILL ONLY GET THE 50% DISCOUNT FOR THE @STRONGANDSXY FITNESS APP VIA OUR WEBSITE STRONGANDSXY.COM YOU WILL NOT GET THE DISCOUNT VIA THE APP STORE!!! PLEASE PLEASE TAKE NOTE OF THIS! 🙏🏼⁣⁣
⁣⁣
✖️MY RECOMMENDATION:⁣⁣
I would advise to go for the @strongandsxy fitness app as it is completely CUSTOMISABLE to you. You receive a meal plan and a training plan and there are LOTS of amazing features to enjoy. Plus we work hard to evolve the app month on month 💪🏼⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🔸15% discount on the long @strongandsxy resistance bands with code STRONG15⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I really hope this helps some of⁣⁣
you stay active. I want to try and help you guys as much as possible while you’re at home. It’s important that we look after our mental health. Going to the gym is our happy place and gives us something to focus on ... well that doesn’t have to stop now! 😊💗⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sending lots of love & positive vibes your way ✨🤗

node.text:
Jamaica 🇯🇲 last year, he had such an amazing aura about him, his message touched our hearts 🥺♥️ ⁣
⁣
Hopefully change will come and one day we can all live in love and unity! 🙏🏼 We have a responsibility to eradicate racism and we need to keep on speaking up to help towards making a change. It’s so upsetting to see what is going on 🥺. But seeing everyone spreading awareness and now taking action towards being anti-racist in their own way (something I am definitely leaning more and more about the last week, there are so many things I didn’t know, it’s really opened my eyes 🙈😭 but I’m working on it) and not just ‘not racist’ is amazing to see. Actions speak louder than words! Racism isn’t born it’s taught and that needs to stop now ✋🏼 We have to use our voices and take real action to make a sustainable change towards equality, fair laws and justice ! It’s insane that this shit is still going on in 2020, what the actual F!! We should be judged on the content of our hearts and not the colour of our skin. The real change most definitely starts from within ♥️ Like @ohhappydani illustration says ‘Until you fix it here ➞ ♥️, and address it here ➞ 🏠, nothing will change here ➞ 🌍’ ⁣
⁣
There should only be one race and that’s the human race 🙏🏼✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿♥️
#blacklivesmatter

node.text:
Throw back photo dump to when I competed in 2017! Which was a great experience and I got to achieve a personal goal of mine (plus I came 2nd which I did not expect!).⁣
⁣
I wanted to push myself out of my comfort zone and have that one time experience learning more about what the body is capable of in different ways. And if we ever had clients who were competing, I wanted to be able to understand what they were going through so I could empathise with them etc⁣
⁣
I was lucky enough to have my husband @romanelanceford coach me through the process and I gained so much knowledge.⁣
First was the bulk phase, where I ate in a calorie surplus (ate more calories than I burnt) whilst practicing progress overload to push my body build as much muscle as possible in the given time. I was able to put on close to 1 stone (14lbs). This was the biggest and strongest I’ve been. ⁣
⁣
Then I did a 10 week cut where I ate in a calorie deficit (consuming less calories than what I was burning), added in cardio and higher volume training. This enabled me to burn the fat and get shredded for the stage. This process was so interesting because how much muscle I could hold onto during the cut was determined by the nutrition aspect more than the training. So having @romanelanceford watch over me daily as my body changed meant that we could implement any changes that were needed.⁣
⁣
The process of the last week was very insightful. Depleting the muscles of glycogen ready for the carb load, followed by tweaks to my water and salt intake to peak just right for the time I was due on! ⁣
⁣
My highest calorie intake during the bulk was 3200kcals per day and lowest during the cut was 1700. Contrary to popular belief I ate carbs every day of my prep, some days as high as 400-500g! Cardio was 60 mins 4-5x per week, weight training 5-6 days. ⁣
⁣
I’ve learnt a lot over the years, more so from experience which is invaluable! And that’s where we’ve been lucky enough to put all of our knowledge and experience into my @strongandsxy fitness app to help you guys achieve your health & fitness goals sustainably, whilst having a healthy balance too because life is all about enjoyment and fulfilment! 💫⁣

Here’s a little shoulder workout for you to try 🙂 enjoy ⁣
⁣
Steering wheels 3 x 15⁣
Front raise variation 3 x 12 ⁣
Upright row 3 x 12⁣
Barbell press variation 3 x 12⁣
Landmine rear delt row 3 x 15 each side ⁣
⁣
You can download my @strongandsxy fitness app where you can try a workout for FREE ! (Before you sign up!) AND enjoy 14 days for free ! strongandsxy.com 📲 ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣
OUTFIT: @gymshark⁣
⁣⁣
Remember to ♥️ and save so I know what content you like to see!
